title: North Korea Launches 23 Missiles, Triggering Air-Raid Alarm in South
description: People on an island took cover as one missile landed near South Korean territorial waters. The South responded by firing three missiles of its own.
dc:creator: Choe Sang-Hun

media:description: A TV screen in Seoul showed news footage from Ulleung, a South Korean island where residents took cover after North Korea fired a missile into nearby waters on Wednesday.
